# Application Test Plan

## 1. Introduction
This document defines the overall testing strategy, scope, objectives, resources 
and timeline required to ensure high-quality delivery of the application.

## 2. Objectives
- Ensure the system meets business requirements
- Verify core functionality works as expected
- Detect functional, usability, performance and security issues
- Minimize production defects and risks

## 3. Scope
### In Scope
- Functional testing
- UI & UX testing
- API testing
- Regression & Smoke testing
- Basic performance validation
- Security awareness checks

### Out of Scope
- Full penetration testing
- Deep load & stress engineering
- Hardware compatibility testing

## 4. Testing Types
- Manual Functional Testing
- Regression Testing
- Smoke & Sanity Testing
- Usability Testing
- API Testing
- Negative Testing
- Compatibility Testing

## 5. Test Environment
- Web application
- Browsers: Chrome, Edge, Firefox
- Devices: Desktop + Mobile responsive
- Tools: Chrome DevTools, Postman, (optional) BrowserStack

## 6. Entry Criteria
- Requirements defined
- Build ready
- Test data prepared

## 7. Exit Criteria
- All critical & high bugs fixed
- Major functionalities tested
- No blocking defects
- Test sign-off completed

## 8. Risk Management
### Possible Risks
- Late requirement changes
- Unstable builds
- Limited testing time

### Mitigation
- Clear communication
- Prioritization of high-risk areas
- Regression focus

## 9. Deliverables
- Test Plan
- Test Cases
- Bug Reports
- Test Summary Report

## 10. Approval
This document requires approval by QA Lead / Product Owner before execution.
